Based on the file contents, I can answer your questions:

1. setup_metric_tensor is defined on line 367 in the private section of the FlatPatch class. 

2. setup_metric_tensor is only called from the constructor (line 67). It's used to initialize the metric_tensor_ member variable with constant coefficients based on the dot products of the basis vectors world_u_ and world_v_.

3. Copying is prevented through deleted copy constructor and copy assignment operator:
```cpp
// Prevent copying
FlatPatch(const FlatPatch&) = delete;
FlatPatch& operator=(const FlatPatch&) = delete;
```
This is likely because FlatPatch contains a unique_ptr member (metric_tensor_) which doesn't support copying by default. Additionally, since FlatPatch represents a geometric entity with potentially large data members (vectors, points), preventing copying helps avoid accidental expensive copies and ensures clear ownership semantics. The class does support moving though, which is more efficient for transferring ownership.

